hacker.jpg\">high res version<\/a> and save for later use?  If you know of any hardcore frugalites you could always sneak onto their computer and save it as their wallpaper ;) I bet they&#8217;d love that&#8230;<\/p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll have to click on over to view the products in detail by month, but here&#8217;s a condensed version for for ya (pay attention to the current Winter things):<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Best things to buy in WINTER<\/span>: Air conditioners, gas grills, houses (for price), luggage<\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Best things to buy in SPRING<\/span>: TVs, houses (for availability), boots &amp; winter gear<\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Best things to buy in SUMMER<\/span>: Big appliances, furniture, laptops, cars<\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Best things to buy in FALL<\/span>: Shrubs, trees, and bulbs (that you can store), car parts, <a href=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/2008\/05\/mrs-budgetsaresexy-on-frugal-wedding.html\">wedding dresses<\/a>, HDTV and home theater equipment.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-size:130%;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Makes sense to me!<\/span><\/span>  Most of these are off-seasonal items. And as <a href=\"http:\/\/lifehacker.com\/5440376\/the-best-times-to-buy-anything-all-year-round\">LifeHacker<\/a> found out,  also times when &#8220;sales are slow, when new products are just about to roll out, or when every single retailer is selling at a discount.&#8221;  Now I just gotta remember this stuff!<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>On Fridays, it&#8217;s beer ;) haha&#8230;okay okay, it&#8217;s really pizza. BUT, if you were ever wondering when to buy other important things (say, like houses,&#8230; <\/p>\n<p class=\"more\"><a class=\"more-link\" href=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/best-time-to-buy-things-with-info\/\">Read More<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":1598